2016 Studying in Canada</h2>
<p align="justify" class="MsoNormal">In the hot study countries, Canada has been
with the low tuition fees, high quality of education, the environment is good,
good welfare to study abroad in addition to the United States and Britain and
Australia in addition to most students want to go to the country, followed by a
comprehensive analysis of 2016 for Canada to study the advantages!</p>
<h1 style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 48px 0px 25px -1.2em; line-height: 1.1; padding-left: 1.2em; position: relative; font-variant: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" class="auto-style1">
English French bilingual environment</h1>
<p align="justify" class="auto-style2" style="mso-para-margin-right: 0.0000gd; mso-para-margin-left: 0.0000gd; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">
<span class="auto-style2">Canada is a bilingual country in both English and
French. Most French-speaking residents (75 per cent) live in Quebec, while
Quebec is located in the eastern part of the country, but there are
French-speaking communities throughout the country. According to a 1991 survey,
French is the mother tongue of 82 per cent of the Québec people and 83 per cent
of Québec's family language. It is estimated that 800 million people speak
English and 250 million speak French. As a bilingual country, Canada can offer
excellent English as a Second Language (ESL) and French as a Second Language
(FSL) for students who wish to study English or French or both.</span></p>
<span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:微软雅黑;color:rgb(0,0,255);letter-spacing:0.0000pt;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-style:normal;font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;">
<h1 style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 48px 0px 25px -1.2em; line-height: 1.1; padding-left: 1.2em; position: relative; font-variant: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" class="auto-style1">
High level of education</h1>
</span></p>
<p align="justify" style="mso-para-margin-right: 0.0000gd; mso-para-margin-left: 0.0000gd; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">
The Government of Canada attaches great importance to investing in education.
Canada's annual education budget is as high as 7.1 per cent of gross domestic
product (GDP). Scholarships will be offered to students with merit, and the
Government will provide loans to help students complete their studies. Compared
with any of the G7 countries, Canada is the country where the average national
income is spent on education. Canada is one of the few countries in the world
with the most complete educational system and the highest level of education. It
is a world leader in business, engineering and science.</p>
<p align="justify" class="auto-style2" style="mso-para-margin-right: 0.0000gd; mso-para-margin-left: 0.0000gd; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">
<span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:微软雅黑;color:rgb(0,0,255);letter-spacing:0.0000pt;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-style:normal;font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;"><o:p>
&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:微软雅黑;color:rgb(0,0,255);letter-spacing:0.0000pt;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-style:normal;font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;">
<h1 style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 48px 0px 25px -1.2em; font-size: 28px; font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;, NSimSun, serif; font-weight: bolder; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(13, 45, 44); padding-left: 1.2em; position: relative; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">
Low cost of studying abroad</h1>
</span></p>
<p align="justify" class="auto-style2" style="mso-para-margin-right: 0.0000gd; mso-para-margin-left: 0.0000gd; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">
Canadian universities, while guaranteeing the quality of education, are slightly
lower than those in other Western countries. Compared to the current four study
countries (the United States, Canada, Britain, Australia), Canada's tuition fees
are more reasonable, and very low, the quality of education is the highest in
the world, but the cost is much lower than those countries . Such as the United
States and the cost of the British annual 250,000 to 300,000 yuan, the cost of
studying in Canada each year (including tuition, living expenses, etc.) about
130,000 to 200,000 yuan, cost-effective.</p>
<p align="justify" class="auto-style2" style="mso-para-margin-right: 0.0000gd; mso-para-margin-left: 0.0000gd; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">
<span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:微软雅黑;color:rgb(0,0,255);letter-spacing:0.0000pt;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-style:normal;font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;"><o:p>
&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:微软雅黑;color:rgb(0,0,255);letter-spacing:0.0000pt;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-style:normal;font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;">
<h1 style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 48px 0px 25px -1.2em; line-height: 1.1; padding-left: 1.2em; position: relative; font-variant: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" class="auto-style1">
Living environment is good</h1>
</span></p>
<p align="justify" style="mso-para-margin-right: 0.0000gd; mso-para-margin-left: 0.0000gd; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">
For many years the United Nations assessed Canada as the world's most livable
country. The top reasons for Canada topping the list are: a sound education
system, high quality of life and low crime rates. As an immigrant country,
Canada has a tradition and policy of encouraging multiculturalism. In addition
to Aboriginal people, Canada has many immigrants from all over the world, and
they live in harmony, fully reflects Canada's national identity is different
from other countries. Canada has strict controls on guns, with one year's crime
rate equal to one month's crime rate in the United States. In Canada schools,
the Government provides 24-hour security services. Canada's learning atmosphere
is relatively easy, young people will have enough space and time to exercise,
entertainment, travel, enjoy the Canadian customs.</p>
